{"id": "EUVD-2020-11970", "enisaUuid": "6743128c-f0ad-392a-8c7f-52b567a618eb", "description": "<p>An elevation of privilege vulnerability exists when Windows Hyper-V on a host server fails to properly handle objects in memory. An attacker who successfully exploited these vulnerabilities could gain elevated privileges on a target operating system.</p>\n<p>This vulnerability by itself does not allow arbitrary code to be run.  However, this vulnerability could be used in conjunction with one or more vulnerabilities (e.g. a remote code execution vulnerability and another elevation of privilege) that could take advantage of the elevated privileges when running.</p>\n<p>The update addresses the vulnerabilities by correcting how Windows Hyper-V handles objects in memory.</p>\n", "datePublished": "2020-10-16T22:18:13", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-04T06:25:01", "baseScore": 8.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H/E:P/RL:O/RC:C", "references": ["https://portal.msrc.microsoft.com/en-US/security-guidance/advisory/CVE-2020-1080"], "aliases": ["CVE-2020-1080"], "assigner": "microsoft", "epss": 0.55, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "65a7cd22-dcf4-31ce-9240-3a7e10ad10b1", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 1809"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "7078faa4-f323-387d-b4a0-64220c7636ad", "product": {"name": "Windows Server 2019 (Server Core installation)"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "92f542d4-96d3-3d19-9838-c534389cdaac", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 1803"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "b9f9c77e-fa2f-3126-a8fe-36dc94069721", "product": {"name": "Windows 10 Version 2004"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "bb7bd549-d108-30d0-87fd-0b1a43302455", "product": {"name": "Windows Server, version 1909 (Server Core installation)"}, "product_version": "10.0.0 <publication"}, {"id": "c0c3f8e5-6d1f-3c4b-85ba-847c9ed5a0d8", "product": {"name": "Windows Serv